          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "BRST"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Bremsstrahlung flux was induced by an electron",
                "linac and a 1-mm tungsten radiator."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A high-purity germanium gamma-ray spectrometer."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The target crucible had a depression drilled on the",
                "face to house approximately 50.9 mg of gallium oxide",
                "powder, or 60 mg for the compressed pellet. Kapton",
                "tape held the powder in place. Then, the remaining",
                "two foils were stacked atop this so as to receive a",
                "nearly identical bremsstrahlung flux. The vanadium",
                "foil was 100 microm thick while the nickel foil was",
                "10 microm thick. The stack was placed 1 cm beyond the",
                "radiator on the beam axis."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Post-irradiation and cooling, the target was",
                "transported to a gamma-ray spectrometer to analyze",
                "the samples individually. The JLab Radiation Control",
                "Department performed a series of HPGe gamma",
                "spectroscopy measurements on the foils in order to",
                "estimate activation. The HPGe detector has a 23%",
                "relative efficiency for 60Co, a beryllium window with",
                "a thickness of 57 mm, and a 49-mm active diameter.",
                "Calibrations for the various foils were determined",
                "via Canberra In-situ Object Counting System Software",
                " (ISOCS)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
